1
00:00:08,600 --> 00:00:10,961
♪Love's little quiz
takes seven parts sweet♪

2
00:00:10,962 --> 00:00:13,559
♪And three parts bitter,
till you and I meet♪

3
00:00:13,560 --> 00:00:17,159
♪I pretend I'm not there,
but secretly stay♪

4
00:00:17,160 --> 00:00:26,399
♪Waiting for you♪

5
00:00:26,400 --> 00:00:31,400
♪We've got so many
romantic dreams to unfold♪

6
00:00:31,480 --> 00:00:36,224
♪Finally hearing
the I love you I long to hold♪

7
00:00:36,225 --> 00:00:39,839
♪Falling fast
into the swirl of your eyes♪

8
00:00:39,840 --> 00:00:42,399
♪It's just too tempting, so tempting♪

9
00:00:42,400 --> 00:00:45,499
♪Never could I have guessed♪

10
00:00:45,500 --> 00:00:46,499
♪My heart's rhythm♪

11
00:00:46,500 --> 00:00:49,632
♪How beautiful it is, meeting you♪

12
00:01:02,975 --> 00:01:05,961
=Late to Love=
(Adapted from "My Husband Is A Billionaire!")

13
00:01:05,962 --> 00:01:08,680
=Episode 16=

14
00:01:15,580 --> 00:01:16,420
Nange,

15
00:01:17,059 --> 00:01:18,700
the site investigation report is in.

16
00:01:18,820 --> 00:01:20,539
Nothing was taken from the lab.

17
00:01:20,619 --> 00:01:23,140
So, it's hard to say what this even was.

18
00:01:23,587 --> 00:01:24,495
(On-site inspection)

19
00:01:25,300 --> 00:01:26,520
(Findings & Recommendations)

20
00:01:27,100 --> 00:01:27,778
What's wrong?

21
00:01:27,779 --> 00:01:29,099
You haven't been yourself

22
00:01:29,100 --> 00:01:30,900
since you got back from the lab.

23
00:01:31,580 --> 00:01:32,739
I'm fine.

24
00:01:34,460 --> 00:01:36,299
Are you scared of something?

25
00:01:36,300 --> 00:01:38,618
Are you afraid of whoever broke in,

26
00:01:38,619 --> 00:01:40,379
or afraid of what might come out

27
00:01:40,380 --> 00:01:41,739
if something was taken?

28
00:01:41,740 --> 00:01:42,819
No.

29
00:01:44,059 --> 00:01:46,659
I've just been tired lately.

30
00:01:47,059 --> 00:01:49,659
Beiyan, please just let me handle this.

31
00:01:52,380 --> 00:01:53,379
Nange,

32
00:01:53,740 --> 00:01:55,140
we're married.

33
00:01:55,380 --> 00:01:56,900
I need you to trust me.

34
00:01:57,020 --> 00:01:58,579
Just because we're married,

35
00:01:58,580 --> 00:01:59,620
I...

36
00:02:01,180 --> 00:02:02,498
I think some things

37
00:02:02,499 --> 00:02:04,379
are better left unsaid.

38
00:02:05,059 --> 00:02:06,780
What do you mean by that?

39
00:02:07,460 --> 00:02:09,259
Beiyan, please stop asking.

40
00:02:09,260 --> 00:02:11,060
Why can't I ask?

41
00:02:11,580 --> 00:02:13,299
Just call me stubborn if you want,

42
00:02:13,300 --> 00:02:14,938
but let me deal with this myself.

43
00:02:14,939 --> 00:02:16,058
Do you really want this?

44
00:02:16,059 --> 00:02:16,859
Beiyan!

45
00:02:19,420 --> 00:02:20,539
Uh, am I...

46
00:02:21,099 --> 00:02:22,819
interrupting something?

47
00:02:23,099 --> 00:02:25,099
Zichen, what are you doing here?

48
00:02:25,539 --> 00:02:27,818
Uncle Beixiang wants to celebrate
Grandma's birthday early.

49
00:02:27,819 --> 00:02:29,019
Just a small gathering at home.

50
00:02:29,020 --> 00:02:31,020
He sent me to invite both of you.

51
00:02:31,779 --> 00:02:33,699
Mrs. Huo, you're looking a bit pale.

52
00:02:34,580 --> 00:02:35,658
I'm fine.

53
00:02:35,659 --> 00:02:37,379
Beiyan and I will be there shortly.

54
00:02:38,140 --> 00:02:38,979
Great.

55
00:02:39,099 --> 00:02:40,139
I brought some bird's nest

56
00:02:40,140 --> 00:02:40,899
for you, Mrs. Huo.

57
00:02:40,900 --> 00:02:41,900
I'll leave it here.

58
00:02:43,059 --> 00:02:43,538
Oh, right.

59
00:02:43,539 --> 00:02:45,299
The old mister has been bringing up

60
00:02:45,300 --> 00:02:46,938
grandchildren again.

61
00:02:46,939 --> 00:02:49,099
He sent me to drop the hint.

62
00:02:50,059 --> 00:02:51,939
Good luck. I'll leave you to it.

63
00:03:01,939 --> 00:03:03,020
Nange,

64
00:03:03,260 --> 00:03:04,938
whenever you're ready to talk,

65
00:03:04,939 --> 00:03:06,379
I'm here.

66
00:03:10,659 --> 00:03:11,740
Don't forget,

67
00:03:12,619 --> 00:03:14,539
you are married to me.

68
00:03:14,580 --> 00:03:16,659
Whatever it is, I can help.

69
00:03:29,900 --> 00:03:32,020
(Still not going to confess?)

70
00:03:32,219 --> 00:03:33,659
(Fine.)

71
00:03:34,499 --> 00:03:37,780
(Then, I'll handle it myself.)

72
00:04:04,339 --> 00:04:05,699
I, Xu Nange,

73
00:04:05,700 --> 00:04:06,938
on this day,

74
00:04:06,939 --> 00:04:08,139
December 17th, 2025,

75
00:04:08,140 --> 00:04:09,900
at 8:52 in the morning,

76
00:04:10,059 --> 00:04:11,498
hereby declare that I

77
00:04:11,499 --> 00:04:12,378
will begin testing

78
00:04:12,379 --> 00:04:14,778
the so-called Alzheimer's drug NIT-33

79
00:04:14,779 --> 00:04:16,019
for its true efficacy.

80
00:04:16,020 --> 00:04:17,459
Based on my prior investigation,

81
00:04:17,460 --> 00:04:19,298
this drug is clearly harmful.

82
00:04:19,299 --> 00:04:22,459
Yet NIT-33 has been sold overseas,
generating billions in profit.

83
00:04:22,460 --> 00:04:23,778
Starting today,

84
00:04:23,779 --> 00:04:25,738
I will expose this massive fraud.

85
00:04:25,739 --> 00:04:27,579
I will use my doctoral studies

86
00:04:27,580 --> 00:04:28,778
as cover,

87
00:04:28,779 --> 00:04:30,259
and publish my findings anonymously

88
00:04:30,260 --> 00:04:32,059
under the alias Dr. X.

89
00:04:32,060 --> 00:04:33,579
The stakes are high.

90
00:04:33,580 --> 00:04:35,340
(Xu Nange.)

91
00:04:36,900 --> 00:04:40,099
(So, you really are Dr. X.)

92
00:04:41,940 --> 00:04:42,699
Mom,

93
00:04:42,700 --> 00:04:44,778
today is your 70th birthday.

94
00:04:44,779 --> 00:04:45,699
Going by the rules

95
00:04:45,700 --> 00:04:48,098
you set for our family years ago,

96
00:04:48,099 --> 00:04:49,459
we're keeping it simple

97
00:04:49,460 --> 00:04:50,780
this year.

98
00:04:52,060 --> 00:04:54,019
Everything our family has today

99
00:04:54,020 --> 00:04:55,819
is all because of the Old Madam.

100
00:04:55,820 --> 00:04:58,780
She built it all from
a single box of medicine.

101
00:04:58,979 --> 00:05:01,298
Without her hard work back then,

102
00:05:01,299 --> 00:05:03,499
none of us

103
00:05:03,500 --> 00:05:05,179
would have the lives we have now.

104
00:05:05,979 --> 00:05:06,780
Come,

105
00:05:07,339 --> 00:05:08,699
let's raise our glasses

106
00:05:08,700 --> 00:05:11,380
and wish the old madam
a very happy birthday!

107
00:05:19,940 --> 00:05:22,700
Back then, the family had nothing.

108
00:05:23,140 --> 00:05:23,978
Grandma

109
00:05:23,979 --> 00:05:26,619
worked as an apprentice
at a nurse's station by day,

110
00:05:26,739 --> 00:05:27,658
while at night,

111
00:05:27,659 --> 00:05:29,459
studied medical texts by lamplight.

112
00:05:29,460 --> 00:05:30,259
Eventually,

113
00:05:30,260 --> 00:05:31,619
she saved enough money

114
00:05:31,659 --> 00:05:34,218
to stock affordable medicines herself

115
00:05:34,219 --> 00:05:36,379
and sell them to neighbors

116
00:05:36,380 --> 00:05:38,059
who couldn't afford the expensive ones.

117
00:05:38,060 --> 00:05:39,298
And little by little,

118
00:05:39,299 --> 00:05:42,340
the idea of going
into medicine was born.

119
00:05:44,900 --> 00:05:45,939
Grandma always used to say,

120
00:05:45,940 --> 00:05:47,499
medicine is for saving lives,

121
00:05:47,700 --> 00:05:49,260
not for making money.

122
00:05:50,620 --> 00:05:51,619
She was right.

123
00:05:51,620 --> 00:05:53,939
And even as the years went on,

124
00:05:53,940 --> 00:05:56,098
and our family business grew,

125
00:05:56,099 --> 00:05:58,659
Grandma never lost sight of her roots.

126
00:05:58,700 --> 00:06:00,699
Mom, do you remember?

127
00:06:00,700 --> 00:06:02,538
You used to instruct the finance team

128
00:06:02,539 --> 00:06:03,858
to make anonymous transfers

129
00:06:03,859 --> 00:06:05,739
specifically to fund

130
00:06:05,940 --> 00:06:08,659
promising students who
couldn't afford medical school.

131
00:06:14,620 --> 00:06:16,579
Grandma did that kind of charity work?

132
00:06:16,580 --> 00:06:17,978
I never heard a word about it.

133
00:06:17,979 --> 00:06:19,139
Neither did I.

134
00:06:19,140 --> 00:06:20,379
What I know

135
00:06:20,380 --> 00:06:22,259
is only the half of it.

136
00:06:22,260 --> 00:06:23,218
Grandma's always kept

137
00:06:23,219 --> 00:06:25,459
a low profile.

138
00:06:25,460 --> 00:06:26,658
She never let me ask

139
00:06:26,659 --> 00:06:28,019
or tell anyone.

140
00:06:28,020 --> 00:06:29,179
All I know is,

141
00:06:29,299 --> 00:06:31,699
there's always been
a fixed outgoing payment

142
00:06:31,700 --> 00:06:33,379
from the company,
and on the transfer slips,

143
00:06:33,380 --> 00:06:35,019
no real name was ever written.

144
00:06:35,020 --> 00:06:36,218
Just a single

145
00:06:36,219 --> 00:06:38,859
letter of the alphabet.

146
00:06:41,859 --> 00:06:42,900
X.

147
00:06:46,500 --> 00:06:49,619
(Nange, I hope this finds you well.)

148
00:06:50,659 --> 00:06:53,859
(Linhai Medical University
is where you should be.)

149
00:06:54,060 --> 00:06:57,220
(Don't worry about tuition
or living expenses.)

150
00:06:57,500 --> 00:06:59,298
(It's all been taken care of.)

151
00:06:59,299 --> 00:07:01,340
(Focus on your studies.)

152
00:07:01,659 --> 00:07:03,659
(You belong here.)

153
00:07:03,820 --> 00:07:05,379
(I know a little)

154
00:07:05,380 --> 00:07:07,379
(of what you've been
through with the Xu family.)

155
00:07:07,380 --> 00:07:10,340
(Being overlooked was never your flaw.)

156
00:07:10,500 --> 00:07:13,899
(It's proof you learned
to stand on your own.)

157
00:07:13,900 --> 00:07:16,658
(Don't underestimate yourself.)

158
00:07:16,659 --> 00:07:19,499
(It has nothing to do
with anyone else's approval.)

159
00:07:20,739 --> 00:07:23,380
(Exhaustion is just part of the climb.)

160
00:07:23,500 --> 00:07:25,259
(But I saw it in your eyes.)

161
00:07:25,260 --> 00:07:28,619
(A flame that refuses to go out.)

162
00:07:28,900 --> 00:07:30,619
(True talent)

163
00:07:30,620 --> 00:07:32,659
(never stays buried.)

164
00:07:32,940 --> 00:07:35,179
(When opportunity comes knocking,)

165
00:07:35,339 --> 00:07:38,059
(I hope you'll be ready.)

166
00:07:40,700 --> 00:07:42,460
(So you remembered me)

167
00:07:42,620 --> 00:07:44,539
(because you already knew)

168
00:07:44,580 --> 00:07:45,979
(who I was.)

169
00:07:46,140 --> 00:07:48,580
(An anonymous letter from years ago.)

170
00:07:48,859 --> 00:07:51,940
(And the tuition and living expenses.)

171
00:07:52,339 --> 00:07:55,099
(Those words that got me through
the Xu family's cold shoulders)

172
00:07:55,219 --> 00:07:57,659
(and all those sleepless
nights in the lab.)

173
00:07:58,380 --> 00:07:59,778
(The mysterious alias I inherited,)

174
00:07:59,779 --> 00:08:01,580
(X.)

175
00:08:02,620 --> 00:08:04,499
(It was Grandma all along.)

176
00:08:05,620 --> 00:08:06,579
Nange,

177
00:08:06,580 --> 00:08:08,340
how did you figure it out?

178
00:08:09,900 --> 00:08:12,260
X is an unknown.

179
00:08:12,620 --> 00:08:14,899
It felt exactly like the kind of thing
Grandma would choose

180
00:08:14,900 --> 00:08:17,260
if she wanted to stay hidden.

181
00:08:22,219 --> 00:08:23,299
That makes sense.

182
00:08:25,339 --> 00:08:26,539
Are you alright?

183
00:08:28,020 --> 00:08:29,140
I'm fine.

184
00:08:33,939 --> 00:08:35,139
Grandma.

185
00:08:36,059 --> 00:08:39,300
Happy birthday.

186
00:09:02,059 --> 00:09:02,940
Beiyan,

187
00:09:03,419 --> 00:09:04,580
I've made up my mind.

188
00:09:06,539 --> 00:09:07,339
There's something

189
00:09:07,340 --> 00:09:09,259
very important I need to do,

190
00:09:09,260 --> 00:09:11,139
and I can't afford
to lose a single minute.

191
00:09:11,220 --> 00:09:12,418
Give me two weeks.

192
00:09:12,419 --> 00:09:13,820
After that,

193
00:09:13,939 --> 00:09:16,298
whether my research is finished

194
00:09:16,299 --> 00:09:18,540
or this matter is resolved,

195
00:09:18,740 --> 00:09:21,019
I'll tell you everything.

196
00:09:21,020 --> 00:09:22,139
I promise.

197
00:09:26,779 --> 00:09:30,099
So what are you planning
to do for these two weeks?

198
00:09:30,980 --> 00:09:32,298
Probably just in the lab,

199
00:09:32,299 --> 00:09:33,940
I guess.

200
00:09:34,299 --> 00:09:35,379
There's a test

201
00:09:35,380 --> 00:09:37,139
I have to run myself.

202
00:09:38,459 --> 00:09:39,460
Okay.

203
00:09:40,020 --> 00:09:41,019
I'll wait.

204
00:09:43,500 --> 00:09:45,899
If you need space, I'll give you space.

205
00:09:46,299 --> 00:09:47,619
If you need time

206
00:09:47,620 --> 00:09:49,219
to sort out what you want to say,

207
00:09:49,220 --> 00:09:50,619
I'll be patient.

208
00:09:51,740 --> 00:09:53,379
But I have two conditions.

209
00:09:53,380 --> 00:09:54,420
First,

210
00:09:54,699 --> 00:09:55,418
make sure you're

211
00:09:55,419 --> 00:09:57,660
eating and sleeping properly.

212
00:09:58,059 --> 00:09:58,899
Second,

213
00:09:59,260 --> 00:10:01,418
if things get dangerous

214
00:10:01,419 --> 00:10:03,458
or too much to handle alone,

215
00:10:03,459 --> 00:10:04,660
call me.

216
00:10:05,659 --> 00:10:07,139
I promise.

217
00:10:29,579 --> 00:10:30,619
Then, I'll

218
00:10:30,620 --> 00:10:31,899
leave you to it.

219
00:10:48,500 --> 00:10:50,818
This is where my brother
and I used to play.

220
00:10:50,819 --> 00:10:51,458
How is it?

221
00:10:51,459 --> 00:10:52,460
Not bad, right?

222
00:10:53,059 --> 00:10:54,339
I have zero interest

223
00:10:54,340 --> 00:10:55,580
in childish things.

224
00:10:55,659 --> 00:10:56,578
Let's get to the point.

225
00:10:56,579 --> 00:10:57,499
Fine.

226
00:10:59,340 --> 00:11:01,859
It's time for the two of us
to come to an agreement.

227
00:11:01,860 --> 00:11:03,099
Once it's done,

228
00:11:03,340 --> 00:11:04,698
we split Huo Group fifty-fifty.

229
00:11:04,699 --> 00:11:06,619
Don't even think about cutting me out.

230
00:11:08,579 --> 00:11:12,099
Honestly, I'm not sure your abilities

231
00:11:12,100 --> 00:11:14,300
are worthy of your ambitions.

232
00:11:14,779 --> 00:11:15,700
Fine then.

233
00:11:16,220 --> 00:11:18,019
Let me give you something concrete.

234
00:11:18,020 --> 00:11:19,658
Xu Nange's research

235
00:11:19,659 --> 00:11:22,220
is targeting Ye
Pharmaceuticals' new drug.

236
00:11:22,340 --> 00:11:23,220
She

237
00:11:24,059 --> 00:11:25,940
is Dr. X.

238
00:11:30,299 --> 00:11:31,420
Proof?

239
00:11:34,020 --> 00:11:35,538
You'll have to verify that yourself.

240
00:11:35,539 --> 00:11:36,499
After all, we're

241
00:11:36,500 --> 00:11:38,139
in this together.

242
00:11:38,380 --> 00:11:40,580
Are you threatening me?

243
00:11:41,179 --> 00:11:42,300
Of course not.

244
00:11:42,900 --> 00:11:43,859
I came in good faith

245
00:11:43,860 --> 00:11:45,379
to propose a partnership.

246
00:11:45,380 --> 00:11:47,739
I'd hate to see my own partner,

247
00:11:47,740 --> 00:11:49,180
Ye Pharmaceuticals go down.

248
00:11:50,260 --> 00:11:51,779
It all depends on whether

249
00:11:51,860 --> 00:11:53,379
Miss Ye is willing to help.

250
00:11:53,500 --> 00:11:54,619
And besides,

251
00:11:56,380 --> 00:11:57,298
I've already identified

252
00:11:57,299 --> 00:12:00,660
the right person to back
and the right moment to move.

253
00:12:01,059 --> 00:12:02,300
Who?

254
00:12:03,179 --> 00:12:04,619
My cousin.

255
00:12:04,659 --> 00:12:06,340
Huo Beiyan.

256
00:12:33,462 --> 00:12:37,236
♪What destiny brought us to meet♪

257
00:12:37,237 --> 00:12:40,557
♪Two different worlds, a love so sweet♪

258
00:12:40,562 --> 00:12:43,936
♪A wish we made
in a past life, it seems♪

259
00:12:43,937 --> 00:12:46,791
♪Destined to cross time and dream ♪

260
00:12:46,792 --> 00:12:50,632
♪Like a fairytale story told♪

261
00:12:50,712 --> 00:12:53,969
♪A gentle breeze feels so bold♪

262
00:12:53,987 --> 00:12:57,673
♪As your hair brushes past your ear♪

263
00:12:57,674 --> 00:13:00,031
♪I long to kiss your cheek, my dear♪

264
00:13:00,032 --> 00:13:04,271
♪All my longing, all my love for you♪

265
00:13:04,272 --> 00:13:06,832
♪Has never changed, it's forever true♪

266
00:13:07,274 --> 00:13:13,672
♪It's the hand of fate
that we meet again♪

267
00:13:14,474 --> 00:13:18,912
♪Let me hold you once again♪

268
00:13:19,162 --> 00:13:22,082
♪Resting against your chest♪

269
00:13:22,432 --> 00:13:27,673
♪Your warmth shines like stars at night♪

270
00:13:27,674 --> 00:13:32,473
♪Let me kiss you once again♪

271
00:13:32,474 --> 00:13:35,273
♪No reason needed♪

272
00:13:35,274 --> 00:13:37,471
♪My heart belongs to you♪

273
00:13:37,472 --> 00:13:43,192
♪I'm not afraid
to cross time to find you♪

